% Lore local da geracao 2
% Formato: pokemon_lore(ID, Texto).
:- multifile pokemon_lore/2.
pokemon_lore(152, 'It loves to bask in the sunlight. It uses the leaf on its head to seek out warm places.').
pokemon_lore(153, 'The scent that wafts from the leaves on its neck causes anyone who smells it to become energetic.').
pokemon_lore(154, 'Anyone who stands beside it becomes refreshed, just as if they were relaxing in a sunny forest.').
pokemon_lore(155, 'The fire that spouts from its back burns hottest when it is angry. The flaring flames intimidate foes.').
pokemon_lore(156, 'Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.').
pokemon_lore(157, 'When heat from its body causes the air around it to shimmer, this is a sign that it is ready to battle.').
pokemon_lore(158, 'This rough critter chomps at any moving object it sees. Turning your back on it is not recommended.').
pokemon_lore(159, 'The tips of its fangs are slanted backward. Once those fangs clamp down, the prey has no hope of escape.').
pokemon_lore(160, 'Although it has a massive body, its powerful hind legs enable it to move quickly, even on the ground.').
pokemon_lore(161, 'When acting as a lookout, it warns others of danger by screeching and hitting the ground with its tail.').
pokemon_lore(162, 'It lives in narrow burrows that fit its slim body. The deeper the nests go, the more maze­ like they become.').
pokemon_lore(163, 'It begins to hoot at the same time every day. Some trainers use them in place of clocks.').
pokemon_lore(164, 'Its extremely soft feathers make no sound in flight. It silently sneaks up on prey without being detected.').
pokemon_lore(165, 'It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.').
pokemon_lore(166, 'In the daytime when it gets warm, it curls up inside a big leaf and drifts off into a deep slumber.').
pokemon_lore(167, 'If prey becomes ensnared in its nest of spun string, it waits motionlessly until it becomes dark.').
pokemon_lore(168, 'Rather than mak­ ing a nest in one specific spot, it wanders in search of food after darkness falls.').
pokemon_lore(169, 'As a result of its pursuit of faster, yet more silent flight, a new set of wings grew on its hind legs.').
pokemon_lore(170, 'Its antennae, whi­ ch evolved from a fin, have both po­ sitive and neg­ ative charges flo­ wing through them.').
pokemon_lore(171, 'This POKéMON uses the bright part of its body, which changed from a dorsal fin, to lure prey.').
pokemon_lore(172, 'It is unskilled at storing electric power. Any kind of shock causes it to discharge energy spontaneously.').
pokemon_lore(173, 'If the impact site of a meteorite is found, this POKéMON is certain to be within the immediate area.').
pokemon_lore(174, 'Instead of walking with its short legs, it moves around by bouncing on its soft, tender body.').
pokemon_lore(175, 'It is considered to be a symbol of good luck. Its shell is said to be filled with happiness.').
pokemon_lore(176, 'Although it does not flap its wings very much, it can stay up in the air as it tags along after its trainer.').
pokemon_lore(177, 'It is extremely good at climbing tree trunks and likes to eat the new sprouts on the trees.').
pokemon_lore(178, 'Once it begins to meditate at sun­ rise, the entire day will pass before it will move again.').
pokemon_lore(179, 'It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.').
pokemon_lore(180, 'Because of its rubbery, electric­ ity-resistant skin, it can store lots of electric­ ity in its fur.').
pokemon_lore(181, 'When it gets dark, the light from its bright, shiny tail can be seen from far away on the ocean''s surface.').
pokemon_lore(182, 'When these dance together, their petals rub against each other, making pretty, relaxing sounds.').
pokemon_lore(183, 'The fur on its body naturally repels water. It can stay dry, even when it plays in the water.').
pokemon_lore(184, 'The bubble-like pattern on its stomach helps it camouflage itself when it''s in the water.').
pokemon_lore(185, 'If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it''s a SUDOWOODO, not a tree. It hides from the rain.').
pokemon_lore(186, 'When it expands its throat to croak out a tune, nearby POLIWAG and POLIWHIRL gather immediately.').
pokemon_lore(187, 'It can be carried away on even the gentlest breeze. It may even float all the way to the next town.').
pokemon_lore(188, 'As soon as it rains, it closes its flower and hides in the shade of a tree to avoid getting wet.').
pokemon_lore(189, 'Even in the fierc­ est wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.').
pokemon_lore(190, 'It uses its tail to hang on to tree branches. It uses its momentum to swing from one branch to another.').
pokemon_lore(191, 'It is very weak. Its only means of defense is to shake its leaves desperately at its attacker.').
pokemon_lore(192, 'As the hot season approaches, the petals on this POKéMON''s face become more vivid and lively.').
pokemon_lore(193, 'It can see in all directions without moving its big eyes, helping it spot attackers and food right away.').
pokemon_lore(194, 'A mucous membrane covers its body. Touching it barehanded will cause a shooting pain.').
pokemon_lore(195, 'Its body is always slimy. It often bangs its head on the river bottom as it swims but seems not to care.').
pokemon_lore(196, 'The tip of its forked tail quivers when it is predicting its opponent''s next move.').
pokemon_lore(197, 'On the night of a full moon, or when it gets excited, the ring patterns on its body glow yellow.').
pokemon_lore(198, 'It hides any shiny object it finds in a secret location. MURKROW and MEOWTH loot one another''s stashes.').
pokemon_lore(199, 'Every time it ya­ wns, SHELLDER injects more poi­ son into it. The poison makes it more intelligent.').
pokemon_lore(200, 'It loves to watch people it''s scar­ ed. It frightens them by screaming loudly or appear­ ing suddenly.').
pokemon_lore(201, 'Because different types of UNOWN exist, it is said that they must have a variety of abilities.').
pokemon_lore(202, 'In order to con­ ceal its black tail, it lives in a dark cave and only moves about at night.').
pokemon_lore(203, 'When it is in danger, its tail uses some sort of mysterious powers to drive away the enemy.').
pokemon_lore(204, 'It spits out a fluid that it uses to glue tree bark to its body. The fluid hardens when it touches air.').
pokemon_lore(205, 'Usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.').
pokemon_lore(206, 'It hides deep inside caves where no light ever reaches it and remains virtually motionless there.').
pokemon_lore(207, 'It builds its nest on a steep cliff. When it is done gliding, it hops along the ground back to its nest.').
pokemon_lore(208, 'The many small metal particles that cover this POKéMON''s body reflect bright light well.').
pokemon_lore(209, 'In truth, it is a cowardly POKéMON. It growls eagerly in order to hide its fear from its opponent.').
pokemon_lore(210, 'It can make most any POKéMON run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.').
pokemon_lore(211, 'When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent''s size.').
pokemon_lore(212, 'This POKéMON''s pincers, which contain steel, can crush any hard object it gets a hold of into bits.').
pokemon_lore(213, 'The fluid secreted by its toes carves holes in rocks for nesting and can be mixed with BERRIES to make a drink.').
pokemon_lore(214, 'With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw arou­ nd an object that is 100 times its own weight.').
pokemon_lore(215, 'This cunning POKéMON hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.').
pokemon_lore(216, 'It always licks honey. Its palm tastes sweet because of all the honey it has absorbed.').
pokemon_lore(217, 'Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.').
pokemon_lore(218, 'These group to­ gether in areas that are hotter than normal. If it cools off, its skin hardens.').
pokemon_lore(219, 'Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.').
pokemon_lore(220, 'It uses the tip of its nose to dig for food. Its nose is so tough that even frozen ground poses no problem.').
pokemon_lore(221, 'Although its legs are short, its rugged hooves prevent it from slipping, even on icy ground.').
pokemon_lore(222, 'The points on its head absorb nutrients from clean water. They cannot survive in polluted water.').
pokemon_lore(223, 'To escape from an attacker, it may shoot water out of its mouth, then use that force to swim backward.').
pokemon_lore(224, 'Its instinct is to bury itself in holes. It often steals the nesting holes of others to sleep in them.').
pokemon_lore(225, 'It always carries its food with it, wherever it goes. If attacked, it throws its food at the opponent.').
pokemon_lore(226, 'It swims along freely, eating things that swim into its mouth. Its whole body is very coarse.').
pokemon_lore(227, 'The feathers that it sheds are very sharp. It is said that people once used the feathers as swords.').
pokemon_lore(228, 'Around dawn, its ominous howl echoes through the area to announce that this is its territory.').
pokemon_lore(229, 'The pungent- smelling flame that shoots from its mouth results from toxins burn­ ing in its body.').
pokemon_lore(230, 'It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.').
pokemon_lore(231, 'During the desert­ ed morning hours, it comes ashore where it deftly uses its trunk to take a shower.').
pokemon_lore(232, 'Because this POKéMON''s skin is so tough, a normal attack won''t even leave a scratch on it.').
pokemon_lore(233, 'This manmade POKéMON evolved from the latest technology. It may have unprog­ rammed reactions.').
pokemon_lore(234, 'The round balls found on the fallen antlers can be ground into a powder that aids in sleeping.').
pokemon_lore(235, 'The color of the mysterious fluid secreted from its tail is predeter­ mined for each SMEARGLE.').
pokemon_lore(236, 'To brush up on its fighting skills, it will challenge anyone. It has a very strong com­ petitive spirit.').
pokemon_lore(237, 'After doing a handstand to throw off the opponent''s timing, it presents its fancy kick moves.').
pokemon_lore(238, 'The sensitivity of its lips develops most quickly. It uses them to try to identify unknown objects.').
pokemon_lore(239, 'It loves violent thunder. The space between its horns flickers bluish- white when it is charging energy.').
pokemon_lore(240, 'It naturally spits an 1100-degree flame. It is said when many appear, it heralds a volcanic eruption.').
pokemon_lore(241, 'In order to milk a MILTANK, one must have a knack for rhythmically pull­ ing up and down on its udders.').
pokemon_lore(242, 'Biting into one of the delicious eggs that BLISSEY provides will make everyone around smile with joy.').
pokemon_lore(243, 'This rough POKéMON stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.').
pokemon_lore(244, 'This brawny POKéMON courses around the earth, spouting flames hotter than a volcano''s magma.').
pokemon_lore(245, 'This divine POKéMON blows around the world, always in search of a pure reservoir.').
pokemon_lore(246, 'Born deep under­ ground, this POKéMON becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.').
pokemon_lore(247, 'It will not stay still, even while it''s a pupa. It already has arms and legs under its solid shell.').
pokemon_lore(248, 'In just one of its mighty hands, it has the power to make the ground shake and moun­ tains crumble.').
pokemon_lore(249, 'It has an incred­ ible ability to calm raging sto­ rms. It is said that LUGIA appears when storms start.').
pokemon_lore(250, 'It will reveal itself before a pure-hearted trainer by shining its bright rain­ bow-colored wings.').
pokemon_lore(251, 'Revered as a guardian of the forest, CELEBI appears wherever beautiful forests exist.').
